  "text": "Molasses are highly abundant sub-products of the food industry that are hitherto being fermented to ethanol at industrial level due to their richness in sucrose. The yeasts employed are adapted strains of S. cerevisiae, that produces high amounts of extracellular invertase, a native enzyme that hydrolyses sucrose into glucose and fructose, and is a Crabtree positive yeast, which means that preferentially ferments high concentrations of sugars to ethanol even under aerated conditions [CITATION_1] .",
